The protest by lecturers at Egerton University against the return of the vice-chancellor through a court order is shocking.The universities are managed by councils and superintended by the Ministry of Education.  As the year comes to a close, it is appropriate to review the challenges and successes that the education sector registered in order to focus on the future.
I wish to start with the disturbing scenario of governance in public universities that for students and parents is anything but inspiring.
In the past, there were isolated cases of members of primary school committees that occasionally used padlocks to lock out headteachers to force their transfer on allegations of poor performance in KCPE exams.



