}



Take extra classes
The universities are managed by councils and superintended by the Ministry of Education.  In addition, the recruitment of vice-chancellors is carried out competitively, and in the last few years, by the Public Service Commission (PSC). The members of the councils are competent and seasoned academicians/administrators and so are senior officials of the ministry and the PSC.
For lecturers to demonstrate in 2020, just like primary school parents of the years gone by,  to express dissatisfaction against their vice-chancellors, when one considers the competencies abounding at the universities,  calls for a review of the management structures and procedures. It does not seem likely that lecturers are wrong all the time.



